.TH "CSSFONTFACERULE.STYLE" "3JS" "November 25, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CSSFontFaceRule.style \- CSSFontFaceRule: style property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]style\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]CSSFontFaceRule\f[R] interface contains a
\f[CR]CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R] object representing the descriptors
available in the \f[CR]\(atfont\-face\f[R] rule\(cqs body.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R] object.
.PP
Although the \f[CR]style\f[R] property itself is read\-only in the sense
that you can\(cqt replace the \f[CR]CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R] object, you
can still assign to the \f[CR]style\f[R] property directly, which is
equivalent to assigning to its \f[CR]cssText\f[R] property.
You can also modify the \f[CR]CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R] object using the
\f[CR]setProperty()\f[R] and \f[CR]removeProperty()\f[R] methods.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example uses the CSS found as an example on the
\f[CR]\(atfont\-face\f[R] page.
The first \f[CR]CSSRule\f[R] returned will be a
\f[CR]CSSFontFaceRule\f[R].
The \f[CR]style\f[R] property returns a \f[CR]CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R]
with the properties \f[CR]fontFamily\f[R], \f[CR]fontWeight\f[R], and
\f[CR]src\f[R] populated with the information from the rule.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]\(atfont\-face\f[R] {
  \f[B]font\-family\f[R]: \(dqMyHelvetica\(dq;
  \f[B]src\f[R]:
    local(\(dqHelvetica Neue Bold\(dq), local(\(dqHelveticaNeue\-Bold\(dq),
    url(\(dqMgOpenModernaBold.ttf\(dq);
  \f[B]font\-weight\f[R]: bold;
}
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myRules = document.styleSheets[0].cssRules;
console.log(myRules[0].style); \f[I]// A CSSStyleDeclaration\f[R]
.EE
